---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Use Cases | BeaconGuard Regulated AI Operations"
  description="BeaconGuard workflow patterns for healthcare privacy review, financial services review, and regulated internal automation."
>
  <section>
    <h1>Use Cases</h1>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is designed for regulated workflows where probabilistic model behavior cannot serve as the authorization boundary.
      It helps teams govern whether AI-assisted actions are allowed, denied, or routed for approval under policy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Priority workflow patterns</h2>
    <div class="section-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Healthcare privacy and operational AI review</h3>
        <p>PHI-sensitive context, user role, and approved AI pathway requirements can be policy-gated before AI-assisted work is allowed to proceed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Financial crime, fraud, and dispute review</h3>
        <p>AML, KYC, fraud, dispute, and account exception workflows can require approval before customer-impacting recommendations proceed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Regulated internal automation</h3>
        <p>Internal tools and AI agents touching regulated systems can be denied or routed for review before action.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Operational patterns</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Policy-gated requests before model execution</li>
      <li>Deterministic allow, deny, or needs-review at the request boundary</li>
      <li>Explicit reviewable evidence for governed workflows</li>
      <li>Fail-closed handling when required policy or trust conditions are not met</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Regulated workflow focus</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is focused on regulated enterprise workflows where authorization, evidence, and control ownership remain explicit.
      It is not a generic AI governance consulting service, chatbot, model host, or GRC repository.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Explore by outcome</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/platform">Understand platform coverage</a></li>
      <li><a href="/trust-assurance">Review assurance model</a></li>
      <li><a href="/deployment">Compare deployment posture</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/design-partner-program">Request governance review support</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Start a platform discussion</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
